          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "**Tracks:** pd-ocr-cli#15\n\n## Context\n\nDiscovered while shipping pd-ocr-cli#15 (security: pin default OCR model revisions + avoid unsafe `torch.load` trust boundary). Model-revision pinning shipped on `fix/security-15-torch-load-pinning` (commit `78dde81`), but the `weights_only=True` half is blocked here.\n\n## Current state\n\nThe inner helpers `_load_det_model` and `_load_reco_model` in `pd_book_tools/ocr/doctr_support.py` already accept an injectable `torch_load` keyword argument — good.\n\n`get_finetuned_torch_doctr_predictor`, however, hard-codes `from torch import load` internally and does not expose a `torch_load` parameter to callers. That blocks downstream callers (pd-ocr-cli, pd-ocr-labeler, …) from enforcing the safe checkpoint-loading path without monkey-patching.\n\n## Ask\n\nExpose a `torch_load` parameter on `get_finetuned_torch_doctr_predictor`, defaulting to something equivalent to:\n\n```python\nfrom functools import partial\nimport torch\n\n# Default chosen so existing call sites become safe without a code change.\n_default_torch_load = partial(torch.load, weights_only=True)  # PyTorch >= 2.4\n```\n\nForward it through to the existing `_load_det_model` / `_load_reco_model` injection points. For older PyTorch (< 2.4), fall back to bare `torch.load` and document the version requirement.\n\n## Why now\n\nPinning model revisions limits *which* checkpoint runs, but the `torch.load` trust boundary still allows arbitrary pickle execution from a compromised checkpoint host. Closing both halves is what makes the original CVE-class fix complete.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- `get_finetuned_torch_doctr_predictor(..., torch_load=...)` accepts and uses the injected loader.\n- A test asserts the default loader sets `weights_only=True` on PyTorch >= 2.4.\n- A note in CHANGELOG / docstring covers the < 2.4 fallback behavior.\n\n## Downstream unblock\n\nOnce shipped, pd-ocr-cli will wire `weights_only=True` via the existing injection points; the placeholder gap test in `pd-ocr-cli/tests/test_security_model_pinning.py::test_upstream_get_finetuned_does_not_expose_torch_load_param` will flip red as the prompt to follow up.",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-24T10:37:09Z",
